      "content": "Originalism, when strictly applied, attempts to ground the amendment's meaning in the text and contemporaneous understandings, which provides a factual anchor to the debate. Conversely, the \"living constitution\" approach allows judges to adapt the amendment's meaning to modern social conditions, which critics see as subjective judicial preference. The factual strength of the originalist argument rests entirely on the robustness and consensus of the historical evidence presented.",
